benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/customFields - Remove custom fields from invoice item

covered: Valid Deletion: Tests TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC06 demonstrate successful removal of custom fields under varied header and parameter scenarios.
Non-Existent Resource: TC08 validates 404 when the target invoice item does not exist.
Authorization: TC19 demonstrates handling of unauthorized access (401) and TC09 demonstrates missing required header leading to 400, covering authorization-related error handling.

Input Validation / Error Handling: Tests TC07 (invalid invoiceItemId), TC10 (malformed customField IDs), TC15 (malicious payload), TC17 (partial valid/invalid IDs) illustrate server-side input validation and error reporting.
Query Parameter Handling: Tests TC02, TC11, TC12, TC18 collectively exercise presence, extra, multiple IDs, and duplicates in the customFields query parameter.

System Resilience & Regression: TC13 (heavy load), TC14 (dependent service unavailable), TC16 (long header values), and TC20 (header parsing regression) probe behavior under stress, dependency outages, and header parsing robustness.
gaps: No explicit concurrency (race-condition) tests for DELETE on the same resource.
No rate-limiting/throttling tests to ensure resilience under high request volume.
No caching behavior tests (ETag/Cache-Control) for DELETE operations.
No 403 Forbidden scenario (authorized but not permitted) tested.
Limited coverage of server error types beyond 503 (e.g., 500 Internal Server Error) tested.
No explicit idempotency checks for repeated DELETE calls.
recommendations: Add a dedicated concurrency test to ensure safe behavior when multiple clients delete custom fields on the same invoice item.
Introduce a 403 Forbidden test to cover authorized-but-not-permitted access paths.
Add rate-limiting tests to verify API behavior under burst traffic.
Add caching validation (ETag/Cache-Control) headers for DELETE responses.
Add tests for 500 Internal Server Error scenarios to complement the existing 503 case, and verify proper error reporting and retry behavior.
